"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"When you buy Bitcoin Cash in a transaction, its price is usually based on U.S. dollars. In other words, you need to exchange U.S. dollars for one unit of Bitcoin Cash. If Bitcoin Cash rises in price, you can sell it profitably because it can be exchanged for more dollars than when you bought it. If you are ready to sell when the price drops, then you will suffer a loss.\\n\\nOn the CMC Markets foreign exchange trading platform, you can conduct bitcoin cash transactions through a CFD account. In this way, you can predict the price trend of Bitcoin Cash without actually buying encrypted digital currency. You don't need to have ownership of Bitcoin Cash. Instead, the price of your open position will increase or decrease based on the price movement of Bitcoin Cash against the U.S. dollar.\\n\\nCFD accounts are leveraged products. This means that you need to pay a percentage of the total transaction volume as a deposit for opening a position. You don't need to directly buy Bitcoin Cash with all your assets at once. On the contrary, you can access a larger amount through the initial deposit. Leveraged trading expands the return or loss because they are based on the total amount of the position.\",\"timestamp\":1636028270,\"title\":\"How to trade Bitcoin Cash?\"},\"digest\":\"KL5MKgfV0zUeSVAVR3gTOA8CJcM_YqkOenh6vNmHtDY\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0xE1045e696DB5c408BBfa6dE026C09b4485ba7ac5\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"U4Bzru7__7dyTvOhs2qCIBRoDL-SV7UNkZA_frJi7UA\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"ICJDNSwhO2DON4b_3-ZOarJotWo8xfLIrjFo3wwVzV4\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"c38WZWIUGtMnVOgZn1bGVjoNPMB_cDOzBTFVPfsnM3J8RQX8_7GAliyld9f8lPWYHQUsO_GPHK40JDLguhdH7w\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0xda79e4d227ac67f93a3748277773a315ac8b0843a7a7353b9fba0eefded95ed1587837a5de89d6fbe9907563b4582ac7007a35815270c6149e45ccab1ec783661b\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize publishing on